    	<h2>Mailing lists</h2>
	<div>
	<ul>
  	<li><p>There is a mailing list for discussion of MTD development:<b><i>
		<a href="http://www.infradead.org/~dwmw2/email.html">linux-mtd@lists.infradead.org</a></i></b>.
	    </p>
	    <p>Please do not post to the mailing list without first reading</p>
	    <ul>
		<li>my <a href="http://www.infradead.org/~dwmw2/email.html">notes on etiquette</a>.</li> 
		<li>the section about <a href="source.html#kernelversions">kernel versions</a></li>
		<li>the <a href="faq/general.html">MTD-FAQ</a></li>
		<li>the available <a href="doc/general.html">documentation</a></li>
		<li>the mailing list archives at <a href="http://lists.infradead.org/pipermail/linux-mtd/">
			http://lists.infradead.org/pipermail/linux-mtd/</a></li>
	    </ul>
	   <p>To subscribe, go <a 
		      href="http://lists.infradead.org/mailman/listinfo/linux-mtd/">
		here</a> or send &quot;<tt>subscribe</tt>&quot; in the body of a 
	    	  mail to <i><a href="mailto:linux-mtd-request@lists.infradead.org">
				  linux-mtd-request@lists.infradead.org</a></i>
	    </p>
	    <p><b>NOTE:</b><br />
		Do not send your subscription request to the list itself.<br />
		Send it to <a href="mailto:linux-mtd-request@lists.infradead.org">
				  linux-mtd-request@lists.infradead.org</a>
		as the above says.
	     </p>
	</li>
